# Project registry  —  name <TAB> host <TAB> dir <TAB> startcmd
# Fields are separated by a real TAB.
#   name      project + tmux session name; what you type to return (pj <name>)
#   host      short hostname (output of `hostname -s`); proj only acts on this host
#   dir       absolute working directory for the session
#   startcmd  command typed into the session's shell on first create
#             (cccc is an example alias for: claude --dangerously-skip-permissions -c)
#
# install.sh copies this to projects.tsv on first install. Then edit it, or use:
#   proj add <name> [dir] [cmd]      (dir defaults to $PWD)
#   proj here [name] [cmd]           (register the session you're sitting in)
example	myhost	/home/me/Projects/example	cccc
